00:08:34.460 --> 00:08:36.970
Teio's serious, then.

00:08:37.750 --> 00:08:39.170
I happened to overhear.

00:08:40.400 --> 00:08:42.470
She's injured pretty badly.

00:08:42.470 --> 00:08:45.630
Even if she heals, she won't not be 
able to run the same way ever again...

00:08:43.230 --> 00:08:46.230
{\an8}Letter of Withdrawal

00:08:46.540 --> 00:08:49.280
If she wanted to keep 
going... keep running...

00:08:49.280 --> 00:08:53.270
If she felt like that, I'd do 
everything I could to support her.

00:08:53.270 --> 00:08:56.690
But if she's given up...

00:08:56.690 --> 00:08:59.970
There might not be anything I can do.

00:08:59.970 --> 00:09:04.670
But somewhere inside, 
I wanna see her running again.

00:09:04.670 --> 00:09:06.110
I can't bear to see her give up.

00:09:06.110 --> 00:09:08.210
I can't get it out of my head.

00:09:08.550 --> 00:09:11.170
Even if she's not as good as she used to be,

00:09:11.170 --> 00:09:13.710
I want another chance 
to see her on the track again.

00:09:14.870 --> 00:09:17.470
But I can tell she's accepted it.

00:09:18.230 --> 00:09:22.150
And I'm her trainer, 
so I can't force the issue.

00:09:23.940 --> 00:09:24.820
What about the others?

00:09:24.820 --> 00:09:26.070
I'm going to tell them.

00:09:26.710 --> 00:09:28.510
It's the least I can do.

00:09:28.510 --> 00:09:32.220
But after everything she's accomplished,

00:09:32.220 --> 00:09:34.080
I don't want her to just 
fade away quietly.

00:09:34.080 --> 00:09:36.450
I really want to send her off with a bang.

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:38.500
Can I get another?

00:09:38.500 --> 00:09:39.650
Two of the same, please.

00:09:39.650 --> 00:09:42.080
And I'm picking up his tab.

00:09:43.130 --> 00:09:44.220
Tonight's my treat.

00:09:45.540 --> 00:09:46.640
Hana-san...

00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:51.960
Say what?!

00:09:51.960 --> 00:09:53.970
Teio's done racing?!

00:09:53.970 --> 00:09:57.360
Yeah. That's why she hasn't 
been coming around lately.

00:09:57.360 --> 00:09:59.850
This is a joke, right?! It has to be.

00:09:59.850 --> 00:10:01.320
This has gotta be rough for her.

00:10:01.320 --> 00:10:05.560
I can't even imagine what it's like, 
not being able to run anymore.

00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:07.170
I'm sure she'll get better!

00:10:07.170 --> 00:10:11.580
She can eat a lot, and get better, 
and then, I know... I think...

00:10:15.410 --> 00:10:18.530
And here I thought no one 
would be around this early.

00:10:18.900 --> 00:10:21.030
Teio-san!

00:10:21.420 --> 00:10:22.520
Teio...

00:10:23.030 --> 00:10:25.960
I'm sorry, guys. I didn't 
mean to make you worry.

00:10:25.960 --> 00:10:28.210
Thanks for telling them, Trainer.

00:10:37.710 --> 00:10:39.680
Teio-san...

00:10:40.280 --> 00:10:43.550
Listen, Teio, can I propose something?

00:10:43.550 --> 00:10:44.300
What is it?

00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:47.680
You know the big fan festival 
that's in September?

00:10:48.010 --> 00:10:50.190
Why don't you perform there?

00:10:51.190 --> 00:10:55.190
You can express yourself to the people 
who supported you this whole time.

00:10:57.360 --> 00:10:58.940
We'll help, too!

00:10:58.940 --> 00:11:01.690
It's the least we can do!

00:11:01.690 --> 00:11:02.340
I'm in!

00:11:02.340 --> 00:11:03.290
Me too!

00:11:03.290 --> 00:11:04.700
Teio-san...

00:11:06.830 --> 00:11:08.350
Thanks, guys.

00:11:08.840 --> 00:11:09.960
Teio...

00:11:12.570 --> 00:11:16.990
I can't believe Teio-san 
can't run anymore!

00:11:13.460 --> 00:11:16.990
Sorry, McQueen. I know 
I'm breaking our promise.

00:11:17.370 --> 00:11:19.720
I'm going to keep running.

00:11:19.720 --> 00:11:24.340
I'll remain the strongest horse girl,
no matter what happens to you.

00:11:25.800 --> 00:11:28.250
Yeah. I think that's for the best.

00:11:28.670 --> 00:11:29.730
Good luck.

00:11:30.590 --> 00:11:31.960
Excuse me, then.

00:11:40.030 --> 00:11:44.030
Umamusume

00:11:40.030 --> 00:11:44.030
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:11:44.030 --> 00:11:46.530
Tracen Academy Fan Appreciation Festival

00:11:46.530 --> 00:11:50.540
9-19
<font color="#1d64df"> Autumn Fan Appreciation Festival</font>

00:12:01.150 --> 00:12:02.560
Good work.

00:12:02.560 --> 00:12:06.070
You're supposed to be working on your starts.
Why are you dashing at full speed?

00:12:06.070 --> 00:12:08.110
I like to start at full power!

00:12:08.110 --> 00:12:10.030
Nothing beats being in 
first for the whole race!

00:12:11.030 --> 00:12:14.870
Just you wait, Teio! I'm gonna 
beat you in the fall race!

00:12:14.870 --> 00:12:17.060
But I'm going to beat Teio first.

00:12:17.060 --> 00:12:20.710
Nuh-uh, it'll be me! I gave her a challenge 
after I won the Tanabata Sho!

00:12:20.710 --> 00:12:21.220
Right?!

00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:22.100
R-Right...

00:12:22.100 --> 00:12:24.340
Wasn't that a while ago?

00:12:24.340 --> 00:12:25.910
Did she ever actually answer?

00:12:27.790 --> 00:12:28.740
Bwuh?

00:12:29.150 --> 00:12:30.400
Right this way.

00:12:29.150 --> 00:12:31.160
Frankfurters

00:12:29.150 --> 00:12:31.160
Candied Apples

00:12:30.400 --> 00:12:32.000
A little bit more...

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:34.330
Lower it slowly, now.

00:12:40.090 --> 00:12:41.050
McQueen...

00:12:41.330 --> 00:12:42.650
How's everything going?

00:12:42.650 --> 00:12:44.960
Thank you for your help, President.

00:12:44.960 --> 00:12:48.300
Everyone is excited to 
see Teio take the stage.

00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:50.060
I'm telling you, we should use this one!

00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:50.810
Spica <font color="#afeacc">Presents:
 </font><font color="#266fef">Tokai Teio 
</font><font color="#ffe753">Special Concert</font>

00:12:50.060 --> 00:12:50.810
No, this one!

00:12:50.810 --> 00:12:54.310
Spica Presents:
Tokai Teio
 Special Concert

00:12:51.050 --> 00:12:53.170
This color is way more Teio-ish!

00:12:53.170 --> 00:12:54.310
No, this one is!

00:12:54.310 --> 00:12:56.190
Would you two give it a rest already?!

00:12:56.190 --> 00:12:57.060
It's her fault!

00:12:57.060 --> 00:13:00.090
Get it together! Are you trying 
to ruin Teio's big moment?

00:13:00.090 --> 00:13:02.200
And are you ever gonna stop crying?!

00:13:02.200 --> 00:13:03.940
Teio-san...

00:13:05.580 --> 00:13:07.200
You seem a little upset.

00:13:07.870 --> 00:13:09.830
I suppose... I am.

00:13:09.830 --> 00:13:13.310
The thought of her leaving me...

00:13:13.310 --> 00:13:17.210
I don't know if I'll be able to 
believe it until it actually happens.

00:13:17.210 --> 00:13:18.330
I feel the same way.

00:13:26.420 --> 00:13:29.590
Okay, it doesn't hurt anymore. 
I should be able to manage—

00:13:29.590 --> 00:13:31.100
I found you, Teio!

00:13:33.920 --> 00:13:35.810
Hey, it's you...

00:13:35.810 --> 00:13:36.680
Double Jet.

00:13:36.680 --> 00:13:39.180
It's Twin Turbo!
You got every word wrong!

00:13:41.090 --> 00:13:44.570
Did you see my challenge? 
When are you gonna race me?

00:13:45.390 --> 00:13:47.570
I'm gonna be in the next All Comers race!

00:13:47.570 --> 00:13:51.210
A bunch of good runners are! 
There's Ikuno, and, uh...

00:13:51.210 --> 00:13:53.540
And, like, Rice Shower, too!

00:13:53.540 --> 00:13:55.290
So we can race there!

00:13:55.290 --> 00:13:58.130
The registration period is already over.

00:13:58.130 --> 00:14:00.430
Besides, I'm not racing anymore.

00:14:00.430 --> 00:14:01.670
Huh?! Why?!

00:14:01.670 --> 00:14:02.980
What do you mean, "why?"

00:14:02.980 --> 00:14:06.400
Okay, then, if I win the All Comers,
will you promise to race me next time?

00:14:06.400 --> 00:14:09.180
That's just it. I'm not 
racing at all anymore.

00:14:09.180 --> 00:14:10.130
No way, no way, no way!

00:14:10.130 --> 00:14:13.980
You have to race me! Cuz I'm gonna win!
 I'll leave you in the dust!

00:14:13.980 --> 00:14:17.190
I'm done with racing. 
You'll just have to give it up.

00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.790
What is that supposed to mean?!

00:14:18.790 --> 00:14:21.560
The real Teio would never 
give up! Never ever!

00:14:21.560 --> 00:14:23.440
What do you know about me?!

00:14:23.440 --> 00:14:25.740
If it can't be done, 
I just have to accept it.

00:14:25.740 --> 00:14:27.910
Even if it hurts so, so much...

00:14:27.910 --> 00:14:29.320
I don't care about that!

00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:31.950
But the Teio I know never ever gives up!

00:14:34.450 --> 00:14:39.110
Rice is racing too, right? And a 
lot of other strong horse girls.

00:14:39.110 --> 00:14:41.070
You can't outrun them all.

00:14:41.070 --> 00:14:44.380
I will win! I'll outrun them all and win!

00:14:44.380 --> 00:14:47.800
You're just a big, dumb jerk, Teio!

00:14:53.060 --> 00:14:56.060
Step, step, jump, then step...

00:14:57.810 --> 00:15:00.390
Teio, you stupid jerk!

00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:04.400
Turbo? What's the matter?

00:15:05.720 --> 00:15:07.400
Ikuno!

00:15:07.400 --> 00:15:09.900
It sucks so, so, so bad!

00:15:09.900 --> 00:15:12.160
So, so, so bad!

00:15:09.900 --> 00:15:12.160
I see... then Teio's giving up.

00:15:12.160 --> 00:15:16.980
I'm gonna do it! I'm gonna outrun them 
all right in front of Teio and win!

00:15:16.980 --> 00:15:19.660
I'm gonna prove what happens 
if you don't give up!

00:15:19.660 --> 00:15:21.650
I don't think you'll be able to.

00:15:22.040 --> 00:15:25.020
The All Comers race is the 
same day as the Fan Festival.

00:15:25.020 --> 00:15:28.340
I don't think Teio will be able to watch you.

00:15:28.340 --> 00:15:29.300
Oh, no!

00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:32.090
Trainer, you have to do something!

00:15:32.090 --> 00:15:33.500
I'm not sure what you want me to...

00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:35.020
No, no, no!

00:15:35.020 --> 00:15:38.100
I wanna show Teio how I run!

00:15:40.970 --> 00:15:42.230
Trainer...

00:15:42.620 --> 00:15:44.160
I'm asking, too.

00:15:44.160 --> 00:15:45.290
Trainer.

00:15:46.620 --> 00:15:47.790
I understand.

00:15:48.700 --> 00:15:50.360
Here's what we'll do...

00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:54.800
First, you'll need to wear these...

00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:55.870
Go! Canopus!

00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:55.870
{\an1}Strike while the iron is hot

00:15:54.800 --> 00:15:55.870
Okay.

00:15:56.890 --> 00:15:58.370
Candle Art

